This is the solution

Task 1. Create a project jumphost instance

You will use this instance to perform maintenance for the project.

Requirements:

Name the instance <b>Instance name</b>.
Use an <i>f1-micro</i> machine type.
Use the default image type (Debian Linux).



Task 2. Create a Kubernetes service cluster
The team is building an application that will use a service running on Kubernetes. You need to:

Create a zonal cluster using <b><filled in at lab start></b>.
Use the Docker container hello-app (gcr.io/google-samples/hello-app:2.0) as a placeholder; the team will replace the container with their own work later.
Expose the app on port <b>App port number</b>.
